        "title": "Java expects a semicolon, when there is clearly one",
        "body": "<pre><code>public class Machine{\n   String machineType;\n   public Machine(String s){ //Sets machineType to String s\n      String getName();\n   }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Why wont this compile? I keep getting a error, saying that its expecting a semicolon, but there is one!<\/p>\n",
