            "creation_date": 1384559597,
            "body": "<p>We cant call methods like this <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> public Machine(String s){ //Sets machineType to String s\n  String getName();    // Method\n }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Instead, assign it to a variable<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> public Machine(String s){ //Sets machineType to String s\n  String var = getName();    // assuming getName returns a string\n }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Even this would work<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> public Machine(String s){ //Sets machineType to String s\n   getName();    \n }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20012706,
            "question_id": 20012684,
            "last_edit_date": 1384560840
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d84b558fd67be10d5a718fb94231909d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 93689,
                "user_type": "moderator",
                "user_id": 256196,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/256196/bohemian",
                "reputation": 427464,
                "display_name": "Bohemian",
                "accept_rate": 77
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1384562245,
            "creation_date": 1384559667,
            "body": "<p>This line:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> String getName();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Makes no sense. Either change it to this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> String name = getName();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Or more likely you want:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public Machine(String s) {\n    machineType = s;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>But I don't know how you could intend that but get the code you got.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20012715,
            "question_id": 20012684,
            "last_edit_date": 1384562245
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cb44bc10dfaaf202886b250b2979ea97?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 29697,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 80449,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/80449/jesper-fyhr-knudsen",
                "reputation": 7987,
                "display_name": "Jesper Fyhr Knudsen"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1384559758,
            "creation_date": 1384559758,
            "body": "<p>It seems like you are trying to call the method <code>getName()<\/code>\nIf that is the case you either have to do:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>getName();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>or <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String name = getName();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Use the first if the method has no return type (void), and the second if it is a String.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20012727,
            "question_id": 20012684
        },
        {
